The paper discusses techniques for reducing the precision of weights and activations in deep neural networks to improve performance and energy efficiency. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses hardware implementation and optimization, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to data compression, which could be relevant to the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.AR).
